  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "Write a poem about the courage it takes to be vulnerable.",
  "response_text": "In the realm where hearts beat bravely, a tale unfolds,\nOf a courage that's not found in tales of old.\nA courage that whispers, not shouts,\nA courage that's vulnerability, in its truest form, unveils.\n\nTo bare one's soul, to show one's heart,\nA journey that's fraught, yet a work of art.\nA dance with fear, a waltz with pain,\nA testament to strength, in every vein.\n\nIn the mirror of eyes, a truth is seen,\nA reflection of a heart, unguarded and serene.\nA testament to courage, in its purest form,\nA testament to love, in every storm.\n\nTo be vulnerable, to be real,\nTo feel the world, to feel the zeal.\nA courage that's rare, a strength untold,\nA story of the heart, waiting to be told.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
